# Our Setup, Import Libaries, Create our Imshow Function and Download our Images
import cv2
import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt

# Define our imshow function 
def imshow(title = "Image", image = None, size = 10):
    w, h = image.shape[0], image.shape[1]
    aspect_ratio = w/h
    plt.figure(figsize=(size * aspect_ratio,size))
    plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

# Load our image as greyscale 
image = cv2.imread('Datasets/images/scan.jpg',0)
imshow("Original", image)

#### THreshold value har qanday bolishi mumkun biz buni tanlab olamiz #######

#Pixel  value<127 dan pasti 0 (qora)ga, value>127 dan balandi esa 255 (oq) ranga aylantiriladi 
ret,thresh1 = cv2.threshold(image, 127, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)
imshow('1 Threshold Binary @ 127', thresh1)

#yuqoridagini teskarisi, value>127 dan balandi oq rang, pixel<127 kichigi esa qora ranga.  
ret,thresh2 = cv2.threshold(image, 127, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY_INV)
imshow('2 Threshold Binary Inverse @ 127', thresh2)

# Values 127 dan balandi kesiladi va qolgan qismi osha rangda ushlab qolinadi.(the 255 argument is unused)
ret,thresh3 = cv2.threshold(image, 127, 255, cv2.THRESH_TRUNC)
imshow('3 THRESH TRUNC @ 127', thresh3)

# 127 dan pasti 0 qora ranga, qolgani esa o'zgarishsiz qoladi (255 is unused) 
ret,thresh4 = cv2.threshold(image, 127, 255, cv2.THRESH_TOZERO)
imshow('4 THRESH TOZERO @ 127', thresh4)

#yuqorini teskarisi, 127 dan past bo'lsa o'zgarishsiz, 127 dan baland bo'lsa 0 ga teng bo'ladi
ret,thresh5 = cv2.threshold(image, 127, 255, cv2.THRESH_TOZERO_INV)
imshow('5 THRESH TOZERO INV @ 127', thresh5)

2. Adaptive Thresholding - MOSLASHUVCHAN THRESHOLDING¶

  1. ADAPTIVE_THRESH_MEAN_C
  2. THRESH_OTSU

cv2.adaptiveThreshold Parameters¶

**cv2.adaptiveThreshold**(src, maxValue, adaptiveMethod, thresholdType, blockSize, C[, dst]) dst

  • src Source 8-bit single-channel image.
  • dst Destination image of the same size and the same type as src .
  • maxValue Non-zero value assigned to the pixels for which the condition is satisfied. See the details below.
  • adaptiveMethod Adaptive thresholding algorithm to use, ADAPTIVE_THRESH_MEAN_C or ADAPTIVE_THRESH_GAUSSIAN_C . See the details below.
  • thresholdType Thresholding type that must be either THRESH_BINARY or THRESH_BINARY_INV .
  • blockSize Size of a pixel neighborhood that is used to calculate a threshold value for the pixel: 3, 5, 7, and so on.
  • C Constant subtracted from the mean or weighted mean. Normally, it is positive but may be zero or negative as well.

#yaxshiroq natija olish uchun play around qilish kerak bu qiymatlar bilan. 

image = cv2.imread('Datasets/images/scan.jpg',0)
imshow("Original", image)

# 127 pasti valuelar  0 ga (black) va undan yuqori barcha valuelar 255 (white) ga aylanadi. 
ret,thresh1 = cv2.threshold(image, 127, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)
imshow('Threshold Binary', thresh1)

# Thresholdingdan avval bluring qilish noisyni yoqotish uchun foydali hisoblanadi. 
#image = cv2.GaussianBlur(image, (3, 3), 0)

# Adaptive thresholding: 3- blocksize neighboorhood  pixellar uchun, 5 - C value hisoblanadi. 
#yaxshiroq natija olish uchun play around qilish kerak bu qiymatlar bilan. 
thresh = cv2.adaptiveThreshold(image, 255, cv2.ADAPTIVE_THRESH_MEAN_C, cv2.THRESH_BINARY, 3, 5) 
imshow("Adaptive Thresholding", thresh) 

#Otsu esa kopincha yaxshiroq natija beradi. boshqa thersholdinglar bilan birga ishlatiladi
_, otsu = cv2.threshold(image, 0, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY + cv2.THRESH_OTSU)
imshow("Otsu's Thresholding", otsu) 

# Blurlarngan rasmdan keyin Otsu thresholdingni qo'llash
blur = cv2.GaussianBlur(image, (5,5), 0)
_, th3 = cv2.threshold(blur, 0, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY + cv2.THRESH_OTSU)
imshow("Guassian Otsu's Thresholding", th3)

3. SkImage Threshold Local¶

threshold_local(image, block_size, offset=10)

The threshold_localcalculates thresholds in regions with a characteristic size block_size surrounding each pixel (i.e. local neighborhoods). Each threshold value is the weighted mean of the local neighborhood minus an offset value

https://scikit-image.org/docs/stable/auto_examples/applications/plot_thresholding.html
